node.text:
Tuany's undeniable faith in her girls, her courage, determination and discipline - all incredibly powerful tools she passes on to them - are a true inspiration. 
She is more than a teacher, she is a compass, showing the girls the dreams they didn't think were possible and paving the path to fulfill them.
They plant the seeds together and  she gets to watch them grow, blossom and flourish on their own. 
This entire project was born from my love and fascination with Tuany, please take the time to watch her episode and I know you will fall in love too.

#IMPACT #WomenofIMPACT
#ShareHerImpact 
@natgeotv

node.title: Meet Tuany, the one who started it all.

node.text:
See how Kelsey handles the biggest loss imaginable and how she embrace the power of the ocean to help others.
See Kelsey's Impact. 

@kelsey___ellis created the Waves of Grief Surf Therapy Programs as part of the Groundswell Community. Through these programs she works with families and individuals to use surfing and the ocean to process their grief and mourn their loss,.
Go to @groundswellcommunityprojec to find out more and to keep their impact wave going. 
#IMPACT #WomenofIMPACT
#ShareHerImpact 
@natgeotv

node.text:
We started working on this unique project over 3 years ago, we searched the globe to find the most extraordinary stories and the most extraordinary women.
One of our main goals was to show how we are all connected, how we all affect each other, how we all can inspire change, how we all can make an Impact.

I am extremely proud to finally share with you the official trailer for IMPACT. 
It follows the stories of six inspiring women making an impact in their communities. 
From Brazil, Puerto Rico, Michigan, California, Louisiana, and Tennessee, their diverse stories are all connected by their unwavering commitment to improving the lives of the people around them.

“National Geographic Presents: Impact with Gal Gadot” premieres April 26 on YouTube and my platforms. 
#IMPACT #WomenOfImpact #CareToShare
 @natgeo @natgeotv

node.text:
It's getting closer...
#RedNotice

Watching the Olympics takes me back to my childhood. Every 4  years my mom would have the TV on ALL day (she’s big into sports being a PE teacher) and we all got so into it. We would bet who’s going to win, followed them from semis to the finals and made a special event of the Olympic Games. 
Now in my home I try to find a way to have a similar experience for my girls. We watched the Olympic games and was amazed by all these incredible athletes.
Some broke records, some broke barriers, some broke our hearts but all of them moved
us so much and showed us the undeniable strength of the human body and soul and the importance of determination and hard work.
You are all winners in our book
Thank you for the inspiration 🙏❤️💪
